BISHKEK, Nov. 16 (Xinhua) -- Kyrgyzstan intends to remunerate citizens who have reported corruption offense, President Sadyr Zhaparov said on Tuesday. One of the anti-graft mechanisms is creating a specialized fund under the Ministry of Finance, from which one-time monetary remuneration should be paid to persons who reported a corruption offense on the basis of a judicial act that has entered into legal force, Zhaparov said at an Anti-Corruption Business Council meeting. "It is also necessary to envisage measures of state support, including financial, to non-profit public organizations carrying out anti-corruption activities, in accordance with the priority areas of anti-corruption activities, anti-corruption education in order to create an atmosphere of intolerance towards corruption in society," he said. Finance Minister Almaz Baketaev said at the meeting that a draft law has been developed to reward financially citizens who reported corruption offenses. Enditem